Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.63,0:00:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So to some degree we walk near the edge.\NYou push your spiritual commitment to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.24,0:00:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the edge.\NAnd if you go over the edge, so you go
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.40,0:00:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,over the edge.\NSo what?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.35,0:00:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So the commitment is a complete and\Ntotal commitment.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.84,0:00:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,When I say if you can find God through\Nthat music, that ecstatic state,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.08,0:00:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,don't stop playing it.\Nround the clock all day, every day,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.44,0:00:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,now and forever.\NAnd when you've transcended that music,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.28,0:00:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you can let it go.\NSo there comes that time when you make a
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.07,0:00:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,run for God.\NThere comes the time when your spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.71,0:00:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,commitment, you know that this is it,\Nthat you're not coming back until you
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.52,0:00:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,get there.\NAnd then you make the final run. We'll
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.44,0:01:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,make the we'll talk about the final run\Nthe last lecture otherwise nobody will
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.32,0:01:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,be here next next time\Nloitating not eating and listening to
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.52,0:01:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,music\Nand their families will be calling the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.72,0:01:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,police. So\Nthe doctor made me do it. I went to his
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.88,0:01:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,lecture and\Nalong the way may one may also get a a
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.20,0:01:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,great number of physical calamities\Nand aches and pains.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.20,0:01:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look up the mystic in\Nencyclopedia,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.20,0:01:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll give you quotes going back to the\N12th, 13th, 14th, 15th century of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.24,0:01:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,various mystics\Nand their description of what they went
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.56,0:01:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,through.\NOne said, "You'll spend more time in
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.20,0:01:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,your sick bed than you will on your\Nknees."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.75,0:02:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that bringing up negative energies and\Nwhat's associated with them and the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.47,0:02:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,karma that's associated with them may\Nput you through all kinds of strange
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.95,0:02:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,wrecks and\Nexperiences that really you need um
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.31,0:02:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,people spiritually advanced who've been\Nthrough them to reassure you as to what
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.31,0:02:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,they are\Nand
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.76,0:02:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,if they seem like a calamity so so it's\Na calamity
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.68,0:02:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what percentage of the way\Nback to God we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.04,0:02:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Um\Nspending time in the presence of a of an
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.48,0:02:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,excellent teacher does have beneficial\Neffects. Yes, we said that's
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.56,0:02:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,vibrational.\NUm, how do you reconcile the contention
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.51,0:02:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that there is no causality with the\Nassertion that one's karma is the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.56,0:03:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,consequence of one's past actions?\NThat's an easy question to see. Um, I
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.95,0:03:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,mean, it's easy to see how it would\Narise because of the mind's proclivity
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.15,0:03:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to translate everything into causality.\NYou see, one thing doesn't cause
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.56,0:03:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,another.\NBut in the quantum reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.87,0:03:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,what's happening is your increasing\Nlikelihoods of potentialities.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.12,0:03:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not causing that.\NBut under this condition, the likelihood
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.20,0:03:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of this happening is increased.\NHowever, in spiritual evolution, freedom
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.72,0:03:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of the will is everpresent.\NOtherwise, there would be no karmic
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.00,0:03:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,merit possible,\Nnor would there be car karmic demerit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.92,0:04:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of spiritual will to say\Nyes to God. Apparently, heaven is
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.00,0:04:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,populated by people who say yes to God.\NYou have to say yes to God to get to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.28,0:04:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,heaven. That's Is that right?\NYou have to want to be there. God
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.04,0:04:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't want anybody\Nwho don't want to be there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.75,0:04:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Who hasn't constant consciously chosen\NGod? That's something I never asked
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.60,0:04:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,before.\NI have permission to ask and resist. And
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.80,0:04:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that's a fact. Heaven God doesn't want\Nanybody in heaven that doesn't want
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.12,0:04:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,them. Okay. It's simple love.\NSo apparently
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.84,0:04:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,karmic mirror comes from having had the\Nopportunity to choose either way and to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.36,0:04:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,have chosen this rather than that. So\Nall is happening by free choice
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.44,0:05:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,not by causal determination.\NYou see if things were causal
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.24,0:05:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,there would be no karmic merit nor\Ndemerit would there? You could just say
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.52,0:05:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,everything's caused by something else.\NWell, this c thought was caused by that
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.47,0:05:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and that was caused by the NBC news and\Nthat was caused by the paper and that
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.03,0:05:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,was caused by what my parents did. So\Nthere's no responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.91,0:05:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither is there freedom. Neither is\Nthere merit nor is there room for
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.96,0:05:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,growth. It's only because you have the\Noption to say yes or no that one by
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.60,0:05:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,saying yes automatically advances\Noneself. I don't know. I didn't set the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.40,0:05:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,whole deal up. Don't ask me about it.\NHow can we learn whether or not we had
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.12,0:05:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,past lives? Well, I suppose you can just\Nask.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.00,0:05:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if we have permission to ask.\NWe have permission to ask. We have
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.19,0:06:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,permission to ask about the person who\Nwrote this. resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.00,0:06:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to know the answer?\N>> Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.72,0:06:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,>> All right. This person did have past\Nhuman lifetimes. Is this? Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.19,0:06:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You can ask. That's the easiest way.\NSee, we said the likelihood is that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.68,0:06:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody in the room had what do we say\Nabout 25 on an average about 25
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.36,0:06:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,lifetimes. See, when you get to a\Ncertain level, you remember them. You
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.96,0:06:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,start to remember them. You begin to\Nsuspect them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.28,0:06:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,There are people who specialize in past\Nlife regression, you know, that can take
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.12,0:06:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you back there and you reexperience it.\NUm, people get it through dreams,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.44,0:06:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,hallucinations,\Nand various other ways. You begin to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.84,0:06:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,suspect it.\NI mean, it's not necessary to know. It's
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.80,0:06:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,not necessary to know. I said you could\Nskip this whole lecture and reach God in
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.31,0:07:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,an instant\Nsoon as you walk out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.00,0:07:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Your spouse will know it because you'll\Nsay, she'll say, "Where am I?" Uh-oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.16,0:07:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,God shock. That was another one they\Nused to bring me. Uh, is this monk in
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.84,0:07:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,God shock? It's Godshock.\NYou hit um unexpectedly a high sator
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.75,0:07:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and it totally blows you away.\NDisoriented. you don't know how to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.63,0:07:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,function in the world. Uh you're\Nconfused, can't think.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.88,0:07:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Um\Nthere's a very major change
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.47,0:07:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and there is actually a period of time\Nwhen you can't function and u so have a
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.19,0:07:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,good place to go away when you reach\Nthat state. pick a nice place in the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.16,0:07:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,country. They they tell them, "If I stop\Ntalking, eating, and looks have a silly
