Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.87,0:08:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we surrender everything to God?\NThe willingness to surrender to God is
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.36,0:08:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of a catch 22\Nbecause
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.68,0:08:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,there is a there is a love for God that\Nis so deep within yourself, so profound,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.16,0:08:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,so exquisitly intense\Nthat for God one would surrender
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.36,0:08:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,anything.\NIt's something to be discovered. It's
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.88,0:08:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,there. That capacity, that willingness\Nto surrender everything to God is innate
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.00,0:08:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,within consciousness.\NWhen you need it and call it forth, it's
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.27,0:08:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,there.\NWould I be willing to surrender this to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.04,0:09:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,God? Yes. Then you get to a tough one.\NSo innate to the pathway of non-duality
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.64,0:09:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,or the Zen barebones\Naesthetic root
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.08,0:09:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,aligned with it is the way of the heart.\NIt is only out of devotion to God, out
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.56,0:09:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of love for God.\NIt is only because of the heart
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.32,0:09:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're willing to follow the\Npathway of negation. I'd say
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.51,0:09:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,out of your love for God, you're willing\Nto let go of a positionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.95,0:09:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So one lets go of\Nthe trit ideas of right and wrong. War
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.04,0:09:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,is bad. Peace is good.\NThere's more crime goes on in peaceful
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.95,0:09:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,times than war. War people are too busy\Nto commit crimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.95,0:10:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,When the war is over, then they go back\Nto it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.27,0:10:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a willingness to surrender all\Npresumptions of the mind and ask God for
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.95,0:10:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,revelation.\NIt's like one holds one's positionality
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.95,0:10:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and ask God to resolve it out of the\Nwillingness to surrender it to God. So
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.27,0:10:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the willingness to surrender things to\NGod comes out of devotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.60,0:10:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,When you get into an really incredibly\Nhigh place of beauty, you'll realize you
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.64,0:10:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,can get in touch with it there.\NIn the state that you're in, you'd be
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.16,0:10:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,willing to surrender\Nanything to God, everything to God, life
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.20,0:10:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,itself.\NAnd in the last instant that is what is
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.88,0:11:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,asked for\Nare you willing to surrender your life
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.92,0:11:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,itself to God.\NSo the more you clear away the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.60,0:11:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,through let's say the Buddhism side of\Nspirituality or the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.80,0:11:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,uh advide the side of non-duality\Nit
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.56,0:11:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,strengthens the way of the heart the\Ntraditional Christian way let's say
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.72,0:11:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,through the heart the more you evolve\Nthrough the heart the greater power you
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.83,0:11:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,have to let go positionalities that are\Ndeeply ingrained.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.39,0:11:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So each one assists the other to be\Ndevoted
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.32,0:11:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to one spiritual work. You're doing that\Nout of your love for God.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.64,0:12:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason to become enlightened is out\Nof your love for God. That's the reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.32,0:12:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It is out of my love for thee, oh Lord,\Nthat I do surrender all that I think and
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.20,0:12:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,believe that I am, including life\Nitself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.56,0:12:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,To thee, oh Lord, do I surrender my\Nbeing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.44,0:12:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's an act of the spiritual will.\Ncomes from the heart of the spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.48,0:12:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,will.\NIt comes out of connecting with the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.44,0:12:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,inner joy.\NWhen you connect with the inner joy, it
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.04,0:12:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,gives you the spiritual power to\Nsurrender anything else except truth to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.39,0:13:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the Lord, you know.\Nalso
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.16,0:13:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,divinity respond let's say no I can't\Nput it that way
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.36,0:13:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the worship of God the love for God the\Ndevotion to God
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.88,0:13:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the love and devotion to spiritual work\Nitself is a sacrifice and a gift to God
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.51,0:13:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,who doesn't need any gifts\Nit's Just a silent speech.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.24,0:13:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a gift of love is a gift of love\Nand it is its own reward.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.68,0:13:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like\Nyou follow something that brings you
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.12,0:13:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,great joy and ecstasy and you tell\Nsomebody about it and then one day you
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.92,0:13:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,can just tell by the look on their face\Nthat they got it. The look on their face
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.92,0:13:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that they got it brings you such joy.\NIt's its own reward. It's
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.19,0:14:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,self-fulfilling. Nothing more is needed.\NCompassion for oneself
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.19,0:14:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,arises out of seeing one's own\Ninnocence. Intrinsically
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.36,0:14:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the innate\Nthat which is within oneself is
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.63,0:14:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,innocent.\NOut of the unmanifest arises the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.56,0:14:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,manifest. Out of the manifest arises\Nconsciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.88,0:14:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And the spirit of God is life.\NLife itself is innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.36,0:14:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes whatever form.\NIt stays life. It does not change with
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.36,0:14:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the form. Huh?\NTo truly love oneself, then it's
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.39,0:14:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,necessary to love God. And to love God,\Nit's really necessary to love oneself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.60,0:15:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So we constantly let go any blocks to\Nthe realization of the truth of that,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.83,0:15:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the willingness to be compassionate, the\Nwillingness to surrender all to God. In
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.04,0:15:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the end, it's a matter of trust and\Nfaith. In the in the end when you are
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.92,0:15:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,asked to walk off the cliff in the end\Nyou're walking off you're going to walk
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.44,0:15:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,off the cliff\Nand it's the faith and trust and the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.07,0:15:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,teachers\Nthe veracity of the teachers the energy
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.36,0:15:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,field of the reverberation\Nthe um absolute conviction
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.19,0:15:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,um of the truth of the Buddha and all\Nthe great avatars.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.24,0:15:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So the last moment when one is asked to\Ngive up the self life and all that you
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.12,0:15:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,know exists\Nthen up comes that
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.24,0:15:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,devotion\Nof enormous power.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.83,0:16:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,One would let oneself be eaten alive if\NGod asked you to.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.80,0:16:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,For thee, oh Lord, do I give myself.\NYou surrender even life itself to thee,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.07,0:16:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,oh Lord.\NUm
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.88,0:16:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the juices of illness and negativity and\Nsuffering
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.36,0:16:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,are\Nthe suffering itself. In other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.80,0:16:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,people look for psychological reasons.\NThere's a naive you see. You see it
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.72,0:16:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,every night on television.\NSort of pop psychology.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.48,0:16:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, this guy just shot 14 strangers in a\Nrow. What do you suppose happened in his
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.83,0:16:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,childhood? That's the first thing. You\Nknow,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.36,0:16:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing.\NNothing that happened in his childhood
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.63,0:16:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,has got anything to do with what he's\Ndoing now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.60,0:17:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just a plausible rationalization\Nbecause we like to psychize things
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.07,0:17:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,because that gives us a superior feeling\Nthat we understand them and can explain
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.48,0:17:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,them when the truth is\Nall these explanations are nonsensical.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.31,0:17:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Have nothing to do with it.\NYou know why I like shooting people?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.40,0:17:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I like shooting people. You\Nunderstand? The payoff is the experience
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.83,0:17:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,itself.\NNot because I'm getting even with my
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.84,0:17:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,father from childhood when he abused me\Nand all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.32,0:17:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Because even if that's a fact, it's\Nstill got nothing to do with why you're
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.40,0:17:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,doing what you do now. You do what you\Ndo now because the experience itself is
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.24,0:17:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the payoff.\NThe experience itself is what is sought.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.76,0:18:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Once we seek to feel sorry for ourself,\Nwe seek to feel resentments and revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.44,0:18:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We love to see with rage and\Nindignation.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.28,0:18:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Ain't that fun?\NJust see, oh, we hate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.03,0:18:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We just have a hate parade. I mean,\Npeople just dig hate. You know, you
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.88,0:18:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,watch those uh\Nnews broadcasts from the Middle East, as
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.12,0:18:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I've spoken before, and you watch how\Nwatch the expression on their face as
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.72,0:18:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,they throw rocks at each other, man.\NThey're really getting off on it. I
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.76,0:18:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,mean, they're having a ball\Npop. I mean, they just love it, you
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.79,0:18:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,know? And you want to get in there with\Na peace sign, get out of there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.32,0:18:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Who wants peace?\Nbe in the middle of a prize fight. Some
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.12,0:18:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,idiot runs out there. Peas,\Ngive us a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.40,0:19:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,How does one surrender the will to\Nthink? That is sort of a tricky one. And
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.88,0:19:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,we've said that thinkingness is its own\Nreward.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.72,0:19:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We just got through saying that the\Nreason behind you see because that's
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.55,0:19:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,based on causality and there is no such\Nthing as causality. So looking for the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.16,0:19:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,cause of something you always end up\Nwith a tautology chasing your tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.20,0:19:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The payoff of an experience is the is\Nthe experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.79,0:19:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the payoff.\NThe payoff of hating is to get to
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.48,0:19:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,experience hating.\NOne can rec retrospectively justify it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.79,0:19:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,My father was brutal to me, etc. But\Nthat frankly is not why you're doing
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.76,0:19:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,what you're doing now. Because you're\Nnot 5 years old. That's not your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.76,0:20:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's got nothing to do with it.\NYou're violent right now because you
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.08,0:20:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,enjoy being violent.\NI've got 50 girls, many of whom just
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.55,0:20:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,enjoy being violent.\NThey like to hit cement walls with their
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.96,0:20:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,fists and fracture their bones.\NIs logic or reason or psychology going
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.60,0:20:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to find a reason? Pathetic. Now you hear\Nthem try to find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.79,0:20:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And I humor them and say, "Uh-huh.\NYou hit your fist against the cement so
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.79,0:20:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you can break your fist and say, "Look,\NI broke my fist against the cement wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.52,0:20:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,See how crazy I am."\NI say, "Look, I know you're crazy. You
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.08,0:20:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,don't have to prove it.\NYou have to break bones to tell me
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.48,0:20:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you're crazy."\NBut what she's saying to me is, "I am
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.55,0:20:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that crazy.\NI am so crazy that I'll actually break
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.40,0:20:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,my bones against cement walls." So I\Nsaid to her, you know, I get it. I get
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.20,0:21:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it.\NYes, you are that crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.48,0:21:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh dear.\NThe payoff of an experience is the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.28,0:21:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,experience itself. Therefore, the only\Nthing you have to experience sacrifice
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.03,0:21:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,is your desire for that experience.\NWe indulge in certain fantasies and
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.91,0:21:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,feelings and recollections and memories\Nbecause of that which it brings up. And
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.76,0:21:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,we're doing it for the sake of that\Nwhich it brings up
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.67,0:21:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and thereby the ego ensures its own\Nsurvival through repetition.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.76,0:21:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We get addicted to being addicting. One\Nof the things you got to let go of is
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.48,0:21:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,wanting to become addicted.\NWe're addicted to thinking. We're
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.48,0:22:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,addicted to suffering. We're addicted to\Nguilt. We're addicted.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.72,0:22:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the things you have to detach\Nfrom is a desire to become addicted to
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.60,0:22:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,things.\NNot addicted to this, not addicted to
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.52,0:22:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that, but\Nbecoming addicted to
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.08,0:22:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,addiction itself.\Nbecoming attached to attachment itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.55,0:22:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people become attached to\Neverything constantly. They're just
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.15,0:22:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,attached to everything. And you just\Nwatch them. They're attached to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.24,0:22:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They're attached to that. Attached to\Ntheir thoughts, attached to their
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.36,0:22:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,habits. They're attached to everything.\NAttached to their possessions.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.52,0:22:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to let go. Not being attached\Nto money, attached to greed, attached to
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.84,0:22:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,six, whatever. You have to let go\Nwanting to be attached period. What do I
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.67,0:22:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,get out of feeling attached to things\Nwhatever they might be?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.72,0:23:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Attachment itself then is some kind of a\Nsecurity operation operating out of
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.00,0:23:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,illusion. So in spiritual work you you\Ntry to find the common denominator so
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.03,0:23:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that when you let go of this down here\Nit lets go a whole lot of things because
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.76,0:23:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have enough time to let go all\Nthe blocks and impediments. What you can
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.20,0:23:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,find is a commonality.\NUh diffuse that commonality and now
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.32,0:23:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,whole rafts of things leave your mind\Nand just never come back there anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.40,0:23:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,People\Nhave good and kindly thoughts about God
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.72,0:23:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and they their heart they touch their\Nheart but
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.76,0:23:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,God is not a sweet old lady. No,\Nthere is a certain parallelism between
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.24,0:23:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the nonlinear and the linear domain\Nbetween spirituality and physicality.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.52,0:24:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, that which is legitimate\Nlegitimately spiritual may also have its
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.76,0:24:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,parallel within the physical domain.\NThe fact that there is a parallel in
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.44,0:24:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,which you can imitate the spiritual by\Nphysical manipulation.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.91,0:24:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a nonssetor to conclude therefore\Nthat the spiritual is unreal because it
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.96,0:24:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,can be imitated within the physical.\NAll kinds of per of experiences can be
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.48,0:24:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,imitated by poking various parts of the\Nbrain.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.20,0:24:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,All kinds of events can be uh imitated\Nspiriously created
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.79,0:24:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and I suppose Indian rope tricks can be\Nperformed.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.60,0:24:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a limited parallelism in which\Nthat which is the imitation within the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.88,0:24:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,physical domain has to the\Nunsophisticated a superficial appearance
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.00,0:25:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to the real.\NOne way to differentiate the truth of
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.32,0:25:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the two is by calibration.\NWe said that out of body experiences for
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.44,0:25:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,for instance\Nare quite amazing
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.08,0:25:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and uh fun. Besides,\Nhow many here have had out of the body
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.32,0:25:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,experience? Yeah. Okay. All right. If we\Ncalibrate the energy of the entity, the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.32,0:25:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,entity. How do you like that? What? What\Ntechnical talking? The person before and
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.15,0:25:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,after.\NWe said I think we've done this before.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.00,0:25:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh out of body experience, the person's\Ncalibration does not uh really change
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.00,0:25:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,significantly. We have permission to ask\Nthat. It it remains about the same
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.00,0:25:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,resistance.\NBut you do learn something. You learn
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.08,0:25:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're more than just a physical\Nbody resist. Now, how come your level of
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.48,0:25:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness doesn't jump when you\Nrealize that? Huh? Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.20,0:26:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,All of a sudden,\Nwhere was it? I was Oh, I'll recall my
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.40,0:26:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,own experience. You know, ser your\Ndeathbed, severely ill, critically ill,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.08,0:26:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,gravely ill,\Nnever even heard out of body experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.36,0:26:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Next thing you know, you're 6 feet in\Nthe air, weightless, invisible.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.44,0:26:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Fantastic. Free as a bird.\NIf you think over there, you're over
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.91,0:26:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,there. You think here, you're there.\NGreat. No time wasted in traveling.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.84,0:26:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, this consciousness advanced as a\Nresult of that experience. Resist. No.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.91,0:26:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not? That's curious.\NOh, I see. The mind discards it as being
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.96,0:26:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,unreal. Resist. Oh, I see. Okay. The\Nreason we don't really grow from it, the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.84,0:26:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind doesn't really believe it. It\Ndiscards it. Even when it's going on,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.27,0:26:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't believe it.\NOut of body is strange, isn't it? Near
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.64,0:27:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,death is something else. Again, that's\Ntransformative and the person's level of
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.79,0:27:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness\Nafter
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.55,0:27:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,near-death experience shows rather\Ndramatic increase. Many people's lives
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.55,0:27:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,changed\Nincredibly. There's a number of
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.55,0:27:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,well-known authors who had near-death\Nexperiences described of total
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.00,0:27:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,transformation that occurred to them as\Na result of those kinds of experiences.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.64,0:27:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And um so that which imitates the\Nspiritual uh does not show. So that
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.88,0:27:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,which imitates a miracle the calibrated\Nconsciousness of it is let's say uh 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.84,0:27:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,very often people want to disprove the\Nreality of spirituality
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.84,0:27:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,are people who hate God and they really\Ncome from very low numbers and um so
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.44,0:27:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that which imitates a miracle doesn't ne\Nnegate the fact that the miraculous
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.55,0:27:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,occurs not only does it occur but it\Noccurs
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.00,0:28:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,very uh frequently and commonly\Nit's just that ordinary perception
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.88,0:28:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't read it because it's outside its\Nparadigm of reality
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.88,0:28:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and I used to be the in the presence of\Nthe miraculous all the time. There was a
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.27,0:28:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,period of time in which the miraculous\Nwas continuous and people would sit down
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.60,0:28:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,in that field and walk uphill and and um\Nand you would see a relative
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.32,0:28:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,uh\Nuh saying, "Well, I told you how long
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.55,0:28:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,you didn't need that cane."\NThe lady could now walk and she couldn't
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.12,0:28:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,walk before. See, but but ordinary\Nconsciousness didn't even read what it
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.39,0:28:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,was. This lady was suddenly able to walk\Nand perfectly fine. you know, you just
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.20,0:28:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,watch you witness the miraculous.\NPeople that that uh are sort of not
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.27,0:28:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,aligned with God don't they they they\Ndon't even see it. They don't see it for
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.12,0:28:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,what it is. But anyway, there's a lot of\Nprograms on TV in which u professional
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.88,0:28:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,debunkers love to try to disprove uh the\Nreality of spiritual phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.52,0:29:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not talking about occult. Occult is\Nsomething else. And uh generally we
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.48,0:29:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,advise people to avoid the supernatural,\Nthe occult, the weird, the strange uh
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.60,0:29:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,channeling, strange chantings of Baba\Nthis and Baba that on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.76,0:29:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And people will do all kinds of astral\Ntricks. It's best to avoid them to stick
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.15,0:29:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,with that which is tried and true.\NSpiritual truth is clear and obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.52,0:29:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't really have to study it. That\Nwhich is
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.36,0:29:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Peace and love committed to truth,\Nintegrity,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.96,0:29:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,surrendering all to God\Nis the same in throughout all time and
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.64,0:29:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,all religions and nothing else is really\Nneeded.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.67,0:29:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,All a teacher can do is be like a coach.\NSee
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.48,0:30:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,coach to affirm the validity of the\Nteaching. Anything that varies from that
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.12,0:30:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is not of God. Anything that tells you\Nkill infidels for God is not of God. Not
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.52,0:30:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of that other than so besides that you\Ndon't really to know need to really know
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.32,0:30:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,anything.\Nuh
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.48,0:30:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the false teachers we've advised about\Nthat too. That's another responsibility
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.72,0:30:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,of a teacher. Two teachers not\Ninterested in money, position,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.12,0:30:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,trappings, ownership, possessions,\Norganizations, hierarchies, titles,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.76,0:30:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,organizations,\Ntreasuries,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.15,0:30:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the owning of anything, the possession\Nof anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.67,0:30:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the proclaiming of anything. There is\Nonly the speaking of the truth as one
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.72,0:30:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,has come to know it through one's own\Ninner experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.20,0:31:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to share that which has been validated\Nthrough
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.44,0:31:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,one's own consciousness.\NAnything else is an artifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.67,0:31:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,This willingness to turn things over to\NGod's will is partly is a result you see
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.39,0:31:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,of your own spiritual will. We're going\Nto stop for a break after this. And we
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.64,0:31:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,described the technique where anything\Nand everything that happens no no matter
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.32,0:31:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,what you stop resisting it and you\Nsurrender it to God. The news says we're
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.76,0:31:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,all going to war. So you surrender it to\NGod. No God, we don't want war. Where's
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.44,0:31:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,my peace sign? Mother,\Nget off it. Without war, how are people
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.72,0:31:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,ever going to get beyond war? The only\Nway to get beyond war is to get beyond
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.72,0:32:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,war.\NYou can't just do it out of a textbook
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.24,0:32:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,in fourth grade. War is bad for people.\NThat should end war, shouldn't it? If
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.67,0:32:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that ended war, there wouldn't be any\Nwar. No, people have to go through the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.00,0:32:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the gut-wrenching, ripping experience of\Ndevastation.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.67,0:32:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What amazes me is the extent to which\Nthe ego has to go before it relents.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.39,0:32:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just amazing the degree, the extent\Nto which the ego will go, the extremes,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.67,0:32:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,barbaric, insane, psychotic degrees\Nbefore it finally lets go of a thing. If
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.72,0:32:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,there's anything I'm dismayed about the\Nhuman condition, that is what it is. I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.20,0:32:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,dismayed that it takes so much to let\Nthe to bring the ego to the level of
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.96,0:32:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,letting go. Why does it have to be so\Nextreme?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.51,0:32:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That distresses me still. So that is\Nsomething I'll have to let go in myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.27,0:33:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That identification with the human\Ncondition.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.39,0:33:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Why it should go to such extremes?\NWhy does it have to go so far? Why does
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.32,0:33:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the pain have to be so bad? Why does it\Nhave to reach? Why does agony have to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.67,0:33:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,take you to the pit beyond which no more\Nagony is bearable and yet you have to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.03,0:33:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,experience more?\NWhy is it so extreme?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.76,0:33:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know. I asked the question\Ntoday. So that's my question for the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.20,0:33:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,day. Why does it have to be so extreme?\NWhy does human suffering have to be so
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.08,0:33:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,enormous?\NWhy does it take 70 million people
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.15,0:33:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,ripped to death by bullets and guns and\Nsavage wounds and their arms and legs
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.51,0:33:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,being ripped off and exploded into\Nnothingness?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.67,0:33:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Not once, but over and over again. 70\Nmillion in one war. 20 years later, you
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.84,0:33:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,got 70 million going in another war.\NEvery 10 or 20 years, another 10, 20,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.24,0:34:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,30, 50, 40, 70 million people go. Why\Ndoes it take such an extreme? Why is it
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.32,0:34:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,so severe?\NWhat does it take for people to wake up
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.15,0:34:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and and recognize a megalomaniac when\Nhe's staring you right in the face
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.56,0:34:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,over and over over again? Whole nations\Nmarch
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.96,0:34:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to some megalomaniac's maniac ego and\Nthey don't recognize it for what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.39,0:34:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is that?\NIt's presented to them over and over
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.87,0:34:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,again within one lifetime. They fall for\Nit one time, 20 years later they fall
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.56,0:34:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,for it again. 10 years later they fall\Nfor it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.07,0:34:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Innately, innately stupid. Well, I guess\Nwe say the ego is innately stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.83,0:34:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It really is dumb, isn't it?\NIt really is dumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.72,0:35:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's the answer. Thank you, Lord.\NPeople are just stupid. Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.88,0:35:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.\NI guess we are dumb lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.76,0:35:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Well,\Nall right. So, that's why the Buddha
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.64,0:35:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,said to become enlightened so that\Nyou're not caught. Oh, I see. Unless you
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.44,0:35:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,grow, you go around and around endlessly\Nin this karmic cycle. Right. Question
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.32,0:35:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,here is, if you reach enlightenment, is\Nit true you don't have to reincarnate?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.00,0:35:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,As far as I know, that's true. Yes. If\Nyou transcend personal karma, but don't
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.83,0:35:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,forget one does not transcend the karmic\Nreality of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.59,0:35:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That that which is God is the totality\Nof all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.80,0:35:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And you may escape your own personal\Nkarma, go into a very neat place, but
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.35,0:35:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you still have not escaped,\Nlet's say,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.24,0:36:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the reality. The allness that exists\Nis the karmic unity of God. So I told
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.24,0:36:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you about that luciferic trap that you\Nhit when you get into a very high place
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.11,0:36:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,where you know you're beyond personal\Nkarma.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.56,0:36:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And then this luciferic knowingness\Ncomes to you. It's non-verbal.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.80,0:36:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that you're beyond personal karma,\Nyou know there is no god to answer for.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.83,0:36:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,answer to. There are nothing and no one\Nto answer to for anything. Nor are you
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.04,0:36:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,accountable\Nbecause there is no personal self that
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.56,0:36:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,could be accountable\Non a certain level of understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.96,0:36:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That certainly sounds true. If there's\Nno personal self, then what would be
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.88,0:36:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,accountable and to whom?\Nwhen it's free of all accountability
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.88,0:36:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is the luciferic temptation at\Nthat level about 840 or something
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.00,0:36:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,own that\Nand you have unlimited power over
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.32,0:37:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,everyone\Nyou have unlimited power over the world
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.20,0:37:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the luciferic temptation now that\Nyou're beyond all personal karma and
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.59,0:37:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,accountability and there is no awful god\Nto punish you for anything anyway that
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.40,0:37:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,was all just an imagination in your\Nego's brain which you've now let go of.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.20,0:37:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,All power is yours.\NThat's the luciferic temptation.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.72,0:37:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And you're all destined for the\Nultimate. So it'll come to you too.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.72,0:37:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't say I didn't warn you.\NHey, I want my money back. You didn't
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.88,0:37:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,tell me about that. I'll tell you now.\NIt's interesting. But the truth that
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.80,0:37:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you've heard from gurus Krishna or\Nwhoever
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.24,0:37:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,walks into that space there's a\Nknowingness not not a voice no script
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.28,0:37:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing there's a knowingness that that\Ntemptation is an error it's an error of
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.83,0:38:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,context at the time you're not\Nconsciously aware of what the error is
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.59,0:38:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,but there is a refusal there's a refusal\Nand then one passes those gates So the
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.48,0:38:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,levels that we see on the board of the\Nhigher levels are guarded by gates and
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.76,0:38:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,each gate there's a question\Nand so I want everybody to know the
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.80,0:38:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,right answers.\NGod looks at your report card and he
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.44,0:38:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,says you got that one right.\NPower over everybody. That's a sucker's
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.32,0:38:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,game.\NOh lordy.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.96,0:38:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, some of these things are beyond me.\NIt's just that they're two circum
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.44,0:39:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,religion is a fascinating subject and of\Ncourse I look into various aspects of it
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.48,0:39:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in the study of consciousness itself how\Nit evolved in the form of religion and
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.92,0:39:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the difficulties that religions present.\NI think the purest purest the purest
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.64,0:39:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual pathway is the fastest way to\NGod
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.40,0:39:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and religions can offer a great deal of\Nhelp along the way. That which is
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.76,0:39:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,positive about the religion, the\Nfellowship,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.96,0:39:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the beauty,\Num the love, the lovingness of the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.28,0:39:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,group, the integrity of the teacher\Nand I myself love going to church.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.83,0:39:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We say when a person\Ndeclares a spiritual intention, is there
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.16,0:39:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,a counterforce? And then we'll stop\Nafter this and take a break and then
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.35,0:39:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll finish up uh after a break. Is\Nthere a counter force? I'm glad you
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.07,0:39:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,asked that. Yes, there is a\Ncounterforce.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.59,0:40:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a counter force. Um,\Nand it's imperative to discover what is
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.28,0:40:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the counterforce.\NYou the counterforce can be quite
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.52,0:40:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,operative, quite effective, and yet in\Nand of itself be a snap to let go of
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.20,0:40:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,once you find it.\NYou can hold the back a whole
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.04,0:40:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,locomotive, you know, with your finger\Non this button here.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.16,0:40:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,4,000 tons of locomotive can't move. One\Nlittle finger, half an ounce. Locomotive
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.59,0:40:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,can't move.\NImmobilize the whole steam engine with
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.72,0:40:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,one little finger.\NSo that's not power. You see?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.72,0:40:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, that's not force.\NIt's the the knowingness. So you may
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.56,0:40:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,discover something in yourself that's\Nreally driving you crazy and it's really
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.83,0:41:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,countered by a very small\Num understanding that little subtle
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.00,0:41:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding. Once you get that the\Nwhole thing clears away of its own. So
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.16,0:41:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,don't be impressed by how difficult the\Nproblem seems to be because its answer
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.92,0:41:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is usually very simple.\Nthe light switch is on this side, not
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.04,0:41:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that side. You go, "Oh,\Nthat's all it was." Many of the major
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.16,0:41:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,ones that I could bypass in my life were\Nreally that simple. But what they
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.76,0:41:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,depended on was a willingness to trust.\NA willingness to trust, to let go of
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.40,0:41:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,what you think you've got for what\Nyou're told will work. You see, so
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.04,0:41:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a certain amount of trust in\Nletting go. But you're right. Whatever
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.72,0:41:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,commitment there is to move in this\Ndirection. It does tend to set up. We we
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.56,0:41:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,tried to cover that in the when we\Ncovered the structure of the ego when we
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.35,0:42:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,talked about the alternative\Nalternatives and the contraries and the
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.28,0:42:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,opposites\Nthat within yourself there things are
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.64,0:42:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,set up as opposites.\NThat's why people feel like they may I
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.68,0:42:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,have a lot of patients. I'm afraid that\Nthey may burst out in the middle of
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.72,0:42:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,church with a curse or a vulgar word.\NThat's a very frequent obsession with
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.92,0:42:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,obsessives. They're afraid that in\Nchurch they're going to suddenly blurt
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.28,0:42:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,out a four-letter word right in the\Nmiddle of mass.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.80,0:42:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So that which is holy and sacred then\Nbrings forward this opposite of that
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.83,0:42:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,which is\Nanti-sacred or whatever you would call
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.68,0:42:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,it, a blasphemy or something. They'll\Nsuddenly blurt out something horrible in
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.16,0:42:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the middle of church.\NSo I suppose we should have a special
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.31,0:42:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,service for them some Sunday morning\Nin which they are free to express
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.31,0:43:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,themselves and we will all clap and\Nparade and thank them for their honesty
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.76,0:43:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and forthrightness and the willingness\Nto share.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.28,0:43:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll take a break and then we'll\Nconclude with some more questions
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.72,0:43:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,afterwards.\NYes, without love, where would we be? At
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.40,0:43:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the bottom of the sea,\Nit takes, you know, a whole slew of
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.07,0:43:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,people to make these events happen.\NWe keep them secret. However,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.56,0:43:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,such pearls are hard to find. We will\Nnot reveal them until the last lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.40,0:43:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But it takes 12 or 15 people working\Naround the clock. I mean, enormous
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.35,0:43:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,amount of energy and work to bring\Ntogether the communications from so many
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.00,0:43:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,people\Nto try to put what we say into a form
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.80,0:44:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,available to others,\Ndistribute them around the world, and
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.68,0:44:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a great deal of work and energy.\NAnd uh, as I say, I'm going to keep them
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.11,0:44:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,secret until the last session.\NUh I wanted to say a few things about
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.83,0:44:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,kinesiology itself not to get carried\Naway with it you know kinesiology is a
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.07,0:44:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,tool it's useful thing and uh a lot of\Ntimes we use it more for curiosity than
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.56,0:44:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,for you know anything really genuine\Nu
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.07,0:44:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you know people ask about other realms\Nand all I mean it's got nothing to do
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.88,0:44:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,with your enlightenment you know what I\Nmean it's just spiritual wandering you
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.64,0:44:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,know and um so you stick to your own uh\Nstraightforwardness.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.59,0:44:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,All that you know has already been\Nspoken and revealed. It hasn't changed
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.31,0:44:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,since\Nit hasn't changed for thousands of
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.52,0:45:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,years.\NThat which was said today, that which
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.28,0:45:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Christ taught, they're all the same.\NBecause anybody who's ever experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.28,0:45:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth, it always comes back forth\Nexactly the same because there is only
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.80,0:45:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,one truth. and unmbellished by\Nthinking this the experience is always
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.40,0:45:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the same. It manifests itself in the\Nsame way. It speaks in the same way and
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.00,0:45:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,one can tell at a glance at a sentence\Nor two by of a book written by somebody
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.76,0:45:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,whe they've experienced it or not. It's\Njust in the energy of the sentence
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.11,0:45:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,itself. It's a way of being with it.\NThere's a conviction that comes only
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.52,0:45:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,from the validity of the experience\Nitself.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.83,0:45:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So the ultimate truth is the ultimate\Nbeyond even experiencing.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.20,0:45:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We said that there's thinkingness.\NThere's that which witnesses the
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.16,0:45:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,thinkingness. There's what that which\Nexperiences the witnessing of the
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.28,0:46:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,thinkingness until finally one gets to\Nthe substrate
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.68,0:46:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,which is consciousness itself.\NAnd then if karmically destined, one
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.64,0:46:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,goes even beyond consciousness itself.\NOut of that which you are arises
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.52,0:46:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness.\NSo the truth, the absolute ultimate
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.72,0:46:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,truth of that which you are is beyond\Neven consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.76,0:46:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's no point to getting wrapped\Nup in kinesiology and making it a new
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.76,0:46:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,obsess obsessive compulsive device to\Navoid reaching enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.07,0:46:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to calibrate everything\Non the planet. It is fun however and of
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.56,0:46:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,course we did it already. We did\Nthousands and we routinely do a thousand
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.96,0:46:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,or two two a year just routinely just\Nwalking through the house various things
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.24,0:46:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,arise. partly because we get such a an\Nenormous amount of communication from
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.07,0:47:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,all over you know all different\Ncountries around the clock all different
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.44,0:47:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,propositions questions\Num would you go here do this etc. So
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.96,0:47:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the difficulty with physicality is um\Nthat you're limited to um the
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.83,0:47:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,temporality of here and now. You see\Nuh with the physical self. Therefore I
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.35,0:47:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,never like the physical self much\Nbecause it's an impediment. It's always
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.04,0:47:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,in the way. When you want to go\Nsomeplace or do something, you got to
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.40,0:47:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,drag this around and that can take hours\Nand days and it's a drag.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.68,0:47:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So I just wanted to say don't make\Nkinesiology itself an obsession or a
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.11,0:47:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,compulsion.\NThat which is necessary to know has
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.11,0:47:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,already been spoken, has already been\Nshared, has already been taught. It's
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.76,0:47:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the same throughout all of time.\NAnything that varies from that which has
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.52,0:47:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,been\Ntaught throughout time is a variance
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.35,0:48:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,from the truth. The truth is always the\Nsame.
